&lt;h4&gt;Intro&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;M0 is the shared infrastructure where businesses launch their own branded stablecoins and financial institutions power them. Built on a common standard, every stablecoin on M0 is interoperable and liquid from day one — giving businesses programmable control over how money moves in their ecosystems, and giving financial institutions the most advanced issuance stack in the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;M0 is seeking a Product Manager to own a core area of the M0 platform end-to-end — and to be accountable not just for shipping it, but for scaling its adoption and revenue. You will report directly to our Chief Product and Strategy Officer and operate with the autonomy of a product leader: setting direction, making hard calls, and partnering with leadership, engineering, design, and go-to-market teams to take products from inception to scale. This is a role for someone at the top of their craft — someone who has built products from zero and grown them into meaningful businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a core product area end-to-end — from discovery and scoping through launch, measurement, and the growth that follows. You own the outcome, not just the release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take products from inception to scale, and own their commercial trajectory — you treat adoption and revenue as first-class product metrics, not someone else&#39;s problem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of our users (builders, issuers, protocols, and institutional partners) and translate their needs into crisp, actionable product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with engineering on technical trade-offs, sequencing, and scoping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship inside regulated, supervised environments, working through risks and constraints without losing momentum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics, instrument what matters, and use data to drive prioritization and trade-off decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with go-to-market, sales and partnership teams to align product launches with customer rollouts and ecosystem growth, and consider build x buy x partner opportunities to advance the roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clearly and frequently — specs, strategy memos, customer updates, launch narratives — to align internal teams and external partners, and raise the bar for how the product org operates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of product management or product leadership experience, with a proven track record of shipping products that made an impact in the market. Equivalent entrepreneurial experience is highly valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to scale a product&#39;s revenue — you&#39;ve owned commercial outcomes and can point to products whose growth you were directly accountable for.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally, deep experience in payments, financial services, or building within regulated or supervised environments — you know how to ship when compliance, licensing, and risk shape the product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical fluency — you are a systems thinker and while you won’t be expected to write code, you are able to hold your own in architectural discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication; you can explain complex systems simply and make sharp prioritization arguments on paper.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical instincts and fluency with data; you know which metrics matter and why.&lt;/li&gt;
